GateDocument.TextWithNodes: PRELIMINARY CALL FOR PAPERS = 20 7 th Workshop on Information Technologies and Systems ( WITS'97 ) Atlanta , Georgia , USA December 13 - 14 , 1997 SPOSNORS : INFORMS College of Information Systems Fisher Center for IT & Management , University of California Berkeley WITS'97 The 7 th Workshop on Information Technologies and Systems ( WITS = 9297 ) will be held in Atlanta , Georgia during December 13 - 14 , 1997 . The purpose of the workshop is to promote discussion and interaction = 20 among members of the Information Systems community with research = 20 interests in cutting-edge information technologies and systems . We are particularly interested in exchanging research ideas and results which will not only contribute to the academic areas , but will also = 20 benefit the business community in the foreseeable future . The theme of WITS = 9297 is the Role of the Internet and Web-based Systems in = 20 Networked Organizations TOPICS We solicit condensed research papers describing original ideas , new = 20 results , novel applications , or "experience reports" describing = 20 lessons learned in the development , operations , and maintenance of = 20 actual systems The research should address issues concerning the = 20 theory , development , management and application of advanced = 20 information technologies and systems . We also encourage proposals = 20 for panels that examine emerging , innovative , or otherwise = 20 provocative issues . Suggested topics include , but not limited to : o Intranet & Extranet Design = 20 o Intelligent Agents o Knowledge Discovery and Management o Information Quality , Privacy and Security o Human- Computer Interaction o Information Warehousing & OLAP o Advanced Database Technologies o Object- Oriented Systems & Methodologies = 20 o Web- Based Software Development & Commerce o Intra- & Inter- Organizational Workflow Systems o Collaborative and Negotiation Systems o Integration with Legacy Systems o Geographical Info Systems o Multi- Media System SUBMISION INSTRUCTIONS The length of submitted papers should be limited to double-spaced , 12 - point font , 10 A 4 pages ( including tables , figures , and references ) . Panel proposals , are limited to 5 = 20 pages , and should include a summary of the topics to be covered , = 20 names , and affiliations of 3 - 4 panelists who have made a = 20 commitment to participate , a summary of their position statements , = 20 and a brief biography of each . A mix of industry and academic panel = 20 members is encouraged Submissions violating the above = 20 requirements will be rejected without going through the review = 20 process . = 20 All submissions , excluding panel proposals , will be = 20 reviewed double blind . Selection for presentation at the workshop = 20 and publication in the proceedings will be based on originality , = 20 contribution to the field , and workshop interest . The program = 20 committee may select papers as posters in which case the authors will = 20 have to condense them to 5 pages for the conference proceedings . = 20 Authors of selected research papers may be invited to submit = 20 complete versions of their work for possible journal publication after = 20 the workshop . All submissions must be electronic in either Microsoft Word , PDF , or postscript files not to exceed 1 Mbyte . The mechanism for the = 20 electronic submissions is as follows . An abstract , including authors names and affiliation , must be e-mailed to wits 97 @ rw . tl . pcrhhi by July 1 , 1997 . A return e-mail will contain instructions and a = 20 paper number that should be used by the authors to e-mail or ftp the "anonymous" full papers . Panel proposals should follow the same = 20 process except the anonymity .
